n%20his%20blog%20this%20week%2C%20Sl%C3%B8k%20said%20he's%20not%20worried%20about%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-ai-boom-recession-citrini-research-layoffs-jobs-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elabor%20market%20doomsday%3C%2Fa%3E%20scenarios%20that%20some%20have%20floated.%20He%20used%20the%20economic%20principle%20of%20Jevons%20paradox%20to%20illustrate%20why.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20steam%20engines%20made%20coal%20more%20efficient%2C%20Britain%20didn't%20burn%20less%20coal%2C%20it%20burned%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20same%20pattern%20is%20happening%20for%20cheaper%20legal%20services%2C%20consulting%20services%20and%20financial%20services.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20introduced%20by%20British%20economist%20William%20Stanley%20Jevons%2C%20the%20principle%20challenges%20the%20assumption%20that%20efficiency%20gains%20will%20always%20lead%20to%20less%20demand%20for%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Jevons%20introduced%20the%20paradox%20in%201865%2C%20Sl%C3%B8k%20says%20that%20it%20is%20still%20relevant%20now%2C%20amid%20predictions%20of%20big%20gains%20in%20productivity.%20He%20sees%20an%20economy%20in%20which%20the%20AI%20revolution%20sparks%20more%20demand%20for%20workers%20across%20industries.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20demonstrated%20in%20the%20chart%20below%2C%20Sl%C3%B8k%20thinks%20AI%20will%20continuously%20drive%20down%20the%20cost%20per%20unit%20of%20professional%20work%20through%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20while%20the%20amount%20of%20professional%20work%20being%20consumed%20will%20skyrocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221366%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20chart%20showing%20the%20impact%20of%20AI%20on%20employment%20from%20Torsten%20Slok.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f1fbb59244129ecb2f936f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETorsten%20Slok%2C%20The%20Daily%20Spark%20-%20Apollo%20Global%20Management%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiving%20AI%20tools%20to%20knowledge%20workers%20will%20lower%20the%20cost%20of%20doing%20some%20of%20these%20tasks%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20noted.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20when%20things%20get%20cheaper%2C%20demand%20goes%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economist%20used%20the%20term%20%26quot%3BJevons%20employment%20effect%26quot%3B%20to%20describe%20what%20he%20sees%20unfolding%20as%20AI%20transforms%20the%20workforce%20by%20making%20it%20more%20efficient%20and%20compelling%20companies%20to%20grow%20headcount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20perspective%20is%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20recent%20views%20of%20some%20market%20commentators%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcitrini-ai-report-labor-market-albert-edwards-dot-com-bubble-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECitrini%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20have%20published%20dire%20predictions%20of%20AI-driven%20employment%20wipeouts%20and%20economic%20stagnation.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20top%20finance%20pros%20are%20in%20Sl%C3%B8k's%20camp%2C%20though.%20Andrew%20Slimmon%20of%20Morgan%20Stanley%20investment%20management%20made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-job-losses-dot-com-bubble-internet-economy-morgan-stanley-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esimilar%20predictions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20highlighting%20the%20possibility%20that%20AI%20could%20be%20a%20major%20job%20creator.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bottom%20line%20is%20that%20cheaper%20inputs%20don't%20shrink%20industries%2C%20Slok%20said.%20%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20AI%20is%20going%20to%20increase%20both%20productivity%20and%20employment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-job-market-labor-unemployment-jevons-paradox-apollo-torsten-slok-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777469300000%2C%22visual%