3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20was%20chief%20of%20staff%20at%20Khosla%20Ventures.%20Here's%20the%20most%20common%20mistake%20people%20made%20in%20job%20interviews.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Left%3A%20Kristina%20Simmons%2C%20Right%3A%20Two%20women%20sitting%20opposite%20a%20table%20as%20though%20in%20a%20job%20interview%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f1d5e83b4f7c3af2b7af75%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESimmons%20(left)%20said%20she's%20looking%20for%20candidates%20who%20follow%20up%20right%20after%20the%20interview.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kristina%20Simmons%3B%20Willie%20B.%20Thomas%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKristina%20Simmons%20is%20a%20former%20chief%20of%20staff%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkhosla-ventures-eric-choi-vc-investor-2025-12%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKhosla%20Ventures%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Today%2C%20she%20runs%20her%20own%20VC%20firm.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20the%20biggest%20mistake%20candidates%20make%20in%20job%20interviews%20is%20being%20inauthentic.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20candidate%20not%20asking%20questions%20during%20a%20job%20interview%20is%20also%20a%20red%20flag%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%2038-year-old%20Kristina%20Simmons%2C%20founder%20and%20managing%20partner%20at%20Overwater%20Ventures.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interview%20stage%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiters-favorite-job-interview-questions-how-to-answer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehiring%20process%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20really%20important%20for%20understanding%20a%20person's%20underlying%20motivations%20%E2%80%94%20what%20makes%20their%20brain%20work%20and%20their%20heart%20tick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20my%20career%2C%20I've%20conducted%20job%20interviews%20with%20prospective%20candidates%20across%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20roles.%20From%202008%20to%202012%2C%20I%20worked%20in%20e-commerce%20and%20digital%20teams%20at%20Lululemon.%20Then%20I%20spent%20roughly%20two%20years%20as%20a%20partner%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandreessen-horowitz-partners-2026-ai-predictions-chatgpt-gemini-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAndreessen%20Horowitz%3C%2Fa%3E.%20From%202017%20to%202021%2C%20I%20worked%20at%20Khosla%20Ventures%20as%20an%20investor%20and%20chief%20of%20staff.%20I%20now%20run%20my%20own%20venture%20capital%20firm%2C%20Overwater%20Ventures%2C%20where%20I%20interview%20CTOs%2C%20CMOs%2C%20AI%20engineers%2C%20and%20more%20for%20the%20companies%20we%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20mistakes%20I%20see%20people%20make%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquestion-recruiter-starts-job-interview-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20interviews%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20what%20candidates%20can%20do%20to%20stand%20out%20from%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229c5bd53d-8db1-4a72-a53c-7cad795567e4%5C%22%3E1.%20Being%20dishonest%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHands%20down%2C%20the%20most%20common%20mistake%20people%20make%20in%20interviews%20is%20not%20being%20authentic.%20It's%20very%20clear%20when%20people%20say%20what%20they%20think%20the%20interviewer%20wants%20to%20hear%20versus%20what%20they%20authentically%20believe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%2C%20during%20an%20interview%2C%20I%20asked%20the%20candidate%2C%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3EAre%20there%20any%20skeletons%20in%20your%20closet%3F%26quot%3B%20because%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhabits-that-make-oprah-talented-interviewer-good-listener-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egood%20interviewer%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20find%20out%20the%20person's%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses.%20The%20person%20said%20no%2C%20but%20then%20I%20did%20find%20skeletons%20in%20their%20closet.%20I%20called%20them%20and%20asked%20if%20they%20could%20explain%20what%20I%20found%2C%20but%20they%20weren't%20honest%20up%20front%2C%20which%20felt%20like%20a%20dealbreaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228680bda6-738d-44bc-85c6-0b7d9417aade%5C%22%3E2.%20Not%20explaining%20the%20'why'%20behind%20their%20career%20moves%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20can%20also%20make%20the%20mistake%20of%20walking%20their%20interviewer%20through%20their%20career%20journey%2C%20and%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20I%20worked%20here%2C%20and%20then%20I%20went%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20without%20explaining%20%3Cem%3Ewhy%3C%2Fem%3E%20they%20made%20those%20choices.%20The%20intentionality%20around%20the%20%3Cem%3Ewhy%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereally%20makes%20a%20difference.%20It%20helps%20you%20see%20whether%20they%20had%20a%20thought%20process%20around%20how%20they%20wanted%20to%20contribute%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20their%20role%2C%20company%2C%20or%20field%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20what%20they%20wanted%20to%20learn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20it%20when%20I%20ask%20a%20candidate%20why%20they%20made%20a%20non-linear%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-change-regret-leads-pr-pro-teaching-business-success-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eunconventional%20career%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they%20have%20a%20good%20answer.%20Maybe%20they%20wanted%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20be%20a%20great%20manager%2C%20so%20they%20took%20a%20job%20you%20might%20not%20expect%20them%20to%20have%20taken%20to%20gain%20these%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f99f09ef-6cd2-4153-b8a4-fc81bee5fc8b%5C%22%3E3.%20Not%20asking%20questions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20red%20flags%20is%20when%20the%20candidate%20doesn't%20ask%20their%20own%20questions%20in%20the%20interview%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20a%20dialogue.%20The%20best%20candidates%20aren't%20just%20being%20interviewed%2C%20but%20they're%20interviewing%20me%20to%20see%20if%20the%20company's%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20them.%20They're%20asking%20questions%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20should%20I%20know%20that%20I%20don't%20know%20about%20this%20company%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20the%20challenges%20at%20this%20company%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223537dc96-b853-48d5-a54f-769d34240030%5C%22%3ECreative%20and%20thoughtful%20candidates%20stand%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20that%20separates%20a%20good%20candidate%20from%20a%20great%20one%20is%20how%20creative%20and%20proactive%20they%20are.%20Once%2C%20at%20Lululemon%2C%20someone%20sent%20us%20a%20rap%20video%20about%20how%20they%20could%20innovate%20the%20company%20to%20try%20to%20get%20our%20attention%20before%20the%20interview.%20It%20really%20stood%20out%20to%20me.%20They%20hustled%20and%20showed%20initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiter-how-to-follow-up-after-job-interview-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efollow-up%20from%20candidates%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20the%20interview%20is%20really%20telling.%20I'm%20looking%20for%20people%20who%20follow%20up%20right%20away%2C%20demonstrating%20that%20they're%20really%20interested%20and%20have%20the%20hunger%20and%20the%20grit%20for%20the%20job.%20I'm%20also%20looking%20for%20thoughtful%20responses.%20Not%20just%20%26quot%3Bthank%20you%20for%20the%20interview%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20something%20that%20will%20make%20me%20learn%20something%20as%20the%20interviewer%2C%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20were%20to%20start%20tomorrow%2C%20these%20are%20some%20ideas%20I%20already%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20job%20hunting%20in%202026%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%